    "text": "As for agency, I see three categories of people:\n1. Those who some agency over computers and want more of it (roughly: us here)\n2. Those for whom computers are tools like many others and who just want more agency in their domain. They often see computers/software as increasingly damaging to their agency.\n3. Those who have no idea that one can actually have agency over computers and who would profit from it if they knew.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1721870703.344739",
    "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
